-- Netflix Names Wells as New CFO, Replacing McCarthy
-- B y   H e a t h e r   B u r k e
-- 2010-12-07T21:33:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-07/netflix-names-wells-as-new-cfo-replacing-mccarthy.html
Netflix Inc. named David Wells as
chief financial officer to succeed Barry McCarthy, who has
expressed a desire to pursue “broader executive opportunities”
outside the company. The change is effective December 10. Wells
joined Netflix in 2004.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
